objects within. She sat down on the floor and rummaged about, pulling some out and laying them on the<br>
carpet. <br>
<br>
In a few minutes, she sat, looking at two old sword blades, archaic in design. Beside them were two rather<br>
ornate sword hilts, encrusted with diamonds, black sapphires, and jacinths. Not particularly her own style, but somehow elegant if only through a respect for ancient traditions of sword-making. In her hand, she held a sealed note for Kargek, in Freeport.<br>
<br>
All that remained was obtaining one of the blades of the spiroc winglord, one more test of her ability to<br>
command, at the least command the respect of others, if not her direct ability to lead others in battle. <br>
<br>
The lesson of the swords was obvious. The original legend spoke clearly as well, if one had ears to listen. No<br>
one does it alone. No one wins alone, conquers alone, is victorious alone. Only in defeat can you be alone.<br>
Glory is to be shared by all. If even the gods of War teach this lesson, it must surely be true.  Learn to work with others, the correct others, in the right way, or fail.<br>
<br>
These bits and pieces here, still needed the scabbard to be combined. Without the binding power, the metal<br>
was useless.<br>
<br>
Yet even the mad lizard, last night, had seen that. He went in alone, but he knew what he was doing when he did, and surely knew the consequences. People said he was mad, but he clearly had achieved something. ... something yet unrevealed, but something. Of course he didn't feel alone, did he? He had said &quot;your support of me here has been enough&quot;, or words to that effect. . . interesting.<br>
<br>
Ayida wondered if attempting to strike at the sun in the sky was mad. Children lept into the air when they saw butterflies fly, why not seek to strike the sun with a sword? &quot;Oh dear, now my thoughts begin to lead me to philosophy, and are incomprehensible ramblings even to myself&quot;. <br>
<br>
Ayida reached back into the trunk, pulled out a dusty, battered, leatherbound book that had clearly seen hard times. Water and blood stains, and others, unidentifiable, marked it. She opened it, and began reading to herself the stories she had written in the days when she had time for such things. <br>
<br>
She turned to the final entries and sat looking at them. Perhaps it was time to begin writing again, so much<br>
had happened since the last time.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=5.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/rust/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm19.emailToFriend?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm19.threadControl?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/rust/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="rage81292frm22">What we do<option value="rage81292frm1">General Discussion<option value="rage81292frm2">Guild Rules<option value="rage81292frm3">Applications<option value="rage81292frm19">Roleplay if ya wanna!</select></td><td><input type=submit value="Go" class=inputbutton></td></tr></table></form></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/brage81292>FI